The '''Stour Music Festival''' is a festival of [[early music]] held in the [[River Stour, Kent|Stour valley]], Kent, England. It was founded by the countertenor [[Alfred Deller]] in 1962. The principal venue is a medieval church, [[All Saints' Church, Boughton Aluph]].<ref name="Life">{{Cite journal |title=Mark Deller and the Stour Festival |url=http://www.kent-life.co.uk/mark-deller-and-the-stour-festival-of-music-1-2228123 |journal=Kent Life (kent-life.co.uk) |access-date=2017-12-23}}</ref>
After the death of Alfred Deller in 1979, his son [[Mark Deller]] continued the festival. In 2012 it celebrated its fiftieth birthday and the centenary of its founder.<ref name="EMS">{{Cite web |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b01hz82f |title=Alfred Deller Centenary |website=Early Music Show. [[BBC Radio 3]]|access-date=2017-12-02}} (Audio, minute 13 onwards)</ref>
